{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, obtaining high-resolution band structures and Fermi surfaces may be crucial, e.g.",
    "to study superconducting instabilities [78] of a doped correlated insulator.",
    "One solution is to use two different momentum meshes, a coarse mesh and a fine mesh, an approach termed Hartree-Fock interpolation [217].",
    "The coarse mesh is used for the HF self-consistency procedure.",
    "After convergence, the Hartree and Fock terms in Eq. 49 are then re-evaluated on the fine mesh with the density matrix on the coarse mesh."
  ]
}